WEBVTT

00:02.085 --> 00:05.214
RYAN: The tableau murders,
Clarke's confession, the firehouse.

00:05.380 --> 00:09.101
- What if it wasn't about Mark's revenge?
- Discrediting the integrity of the FBI.

00:09.301 --> 00:12.180
This is about the trial.
This is about Strauss.

00:12.387 --> 00:13.479
We've had a setback.

00:14.264 --> 00:16.733
Gina called me.
She told me about the threats.

00:16.934 --> 00:20.279
- First Clarke, now your brother's
firehouse. RYAN: I'm worried about Max.

00:20.479 --> 00:23.949
- I'm worried about you.
- If there was something to tell you, I would.

00:24.149 --> 00:27.369
We're gearing up to hit you where you live.
You and that niece of yours.

00:27.528 --> 00:30.202
- Tom deserves better than this.
- Tom deserves the truth.

00:30.405 --> 00:33.500
In a moment of weakness, I slept with you.
I really shouldn't have.

00:33.700 --> 00:35.794
I cannot afford to have you
crossing the line.

00:35.994 --> 00:38.338
I won't. I'm not denying
I have a personal stake...

00:38.539 --> 00:40.962
...in bringing Mark in,
but I won't let it interfere.

00:41.166 --> 00:44.591
He'll gut us in our sleep if he even
suspects that we have our own agenda.

00:44.795 --> 00:46.718
Call Juliana. We need to get out of town.

00:46.922 --> 00:48.469
Too bad. We're on a schedule.

00:49.675 --> 00:52.349
DAISY: Kyle has been shot.
Please, okay? You saved my life.

00:52.553 --> 00:55.853
- Why would I turn on you? Please, help?
- Yeah, okay, okay.

00:56.056 --> 00:57.524
Okay, I'll text you an address.

01:14.408 --> 01:16.877
STRAUSS:
Agent Hardy, what a surprise.

01:17.077 --> 01:18.750
Does my attorney know you're here?

01:18.954 --> 01:20.456
Oh, I'm not really here, doctor.

01:20.664 --> 01:22.257
This bus is officially empty.

01:22.749 --> 01:27.095
Just you and your conscience,
taking the long drive to judgment day.

01:27.296 --> 01:29.173
Well, well.

01:29.381 --> 01:30.928
Someone's feeling confident.

01:32.718 --> 01:34.015
Your students failed.

01:34.219 --> 01:38.315
Your plan to discredit me
and the case against you, that didn't take.

01:39.641 --> 01:43.737
Sadly, I haven't the faintest idea
what you're talking about.

01:43.937 --> 01:45.610
Okay. I get it now.

01:45.814 --> 01:49.114
You can't give me anything
I would use against you on the stand today.

01:49.526 --> 01:54.123
But see, what you don't seem
to understand, doctor...

01:54.323 --> 01:56.121
...is that your fate's already sealed.

01:56.825 --> 01:59.248
There's no going back to the way it was...

01:59.453 --> 02:03.959
...no more mentoring killers
from the comfort of your mansion.

02:04.166 --> 02:06.260
The truth is about to come out.

02:06.460 --> 02:10.840
And the world is gonna see you
for the pathetic little psychopath...

02:11.048 --> 02:13.301
...that you really are.

02:15.844 --> 02:18.688
The truth is a tricky thing, Agent Hardy.

02:18.889 --> 02:21.813
You think it's a weapon you can aim at me.

02:22.225 --> 02:25.195
But it's just as likely
to blow up in your face.

02:27.564 --> 02:29.362
See you in court.

02:39.368 --> 02:41.837
MAN [ON TV]: And once again
recapping our top news story...

02:42.037 --> 02:45.917
yesterday's early-morning raid in Brooklyn
failed to capture Mark Gray...

02:46.124 --> 02:49.298
...but federal officials are confident
that his arrest...

02:49.503 --> 02:53.098
...as well as that of Daisy and Kyle Locke,
is imminent.

02:53.298 --> 02:55.642
Should you or anyone you know
spot any of these...

02:55.842 --> 02:58.265
His fever is getting worse.

02:58.804 --> 03:03.184
- I think the wound is getting infected.
- Yeah, getting shot is no joke.

03:03.392 --> 03:05.770
...Contact authorities immediately.

03:05.977 --> 03:09.197
Keep it right here
for all the late-breaking details.

03:09.398 --> 03:13.403
Mark, please. I don't know how
long he can last like this.

03:14.194 --> 03:17.118
We need more medical supplies,
bandages, antiseptic.

03:17.280 --> 03:19.578
- So go get them.
- I don't wanna leave him.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.579
Please.

03:23.954 --> 03:26.753
I know, I have no right to ask you to go...

03:27.749 --> 03:32.505
...but I don't know if I could live with myself
if something happened to him while I was gone.

03:36.049 --> 03:37.392
I know that you understand.

03:47.561 --> 03:48.733
Thank you.

04:04.828 --> 04:06.501
[KYLE GRUNTS]

04:08.081 --> 04:11.631
Maybe you should stay here.
You could still get an infection.

04:11.835 --> 04:13.052
Forget it.

04:13.253 --> 04:15.005
No way I'm letting you do this alone.

04:25.098 --> 04:26.395
Okay, he's gone.

04:28.643 --> 04:30.645
We need to get you some real pain meds.

04:31.480 --> 04:32.652
I'll be fine.

04:32.856 --> 04:35.735
We just need to keep it together
for one more day.

04:36.443 --> 04:38.445
Then we're home free.

04:38.653 --> 04:40.371
A new life.

04:40.989 --> 04:43.333
Have you thought
about who you wanna be yet?

04:43.992 --> 04:45.915
Doesn't matter.

04:46.787 --> 04:49.631
As long as I'm with you, I'll be happy.

04:49.998 --> 04:52.547
Come on. Juliana's waiting.

05:00.801 --> 05:02.053
MARK:
Go ahead, say it.

05:02.260 --> 05:03.512
"I told you so."

05:03.720 --> 05:05.563
Ah, come on, Mark, don't be like that.

05:05.722 --> 05:07.349
You gotta look at the bright side.

05:07.557 --> 05:09.184
There is no bright side.

05:09.392 --> 05:13.272
I'm so stupid. I thought they were my
friends, trying to help us get our revenge...

05:13.480 --> 05:16.609
Hey, hey, hey. You're
not stupid, all right?

05:16.817 --> 05:18.410
You just have a big heart.

05:19.194 --> 05:22.539
Come on, you need to toughen up,
find out what the hell they're up to.

05:40.549 --> 05:44.395
Reyes, conference room, 10 minutes. Agent
Hardy wants to go over the protocols...

05:44.594 --> 05:46.267
...for the Strauss trial.
- Got it.

05:46.471 --> 05:47.518
Have you seen Max?

05:47.722 --> 05:49.565
Uh, no, I don't think she's in yet.

05:49.724 --> 05:50.941
But I'll give her a call.

05:56.398 --> 05:59.618
[LINE RINGING
& CELL PHONE RINGING ON COMPUTER]

06:05.115 --> 06:06.287
[LINE BEEPS]

06:17.002 --> 06:19.926
I'm sorry, this is all very impressive...

06:20.130 --> 06:22.974
...but it's way outside of our
comfort zone. And Kyle's hurt.

06:23.174 --> 06:24.892
- I'm fine, Daisy.
JULIANA: I hope so.

06:25.302 --> 06:29.432
- Because there's no room for mistakes today.
- We'll get it done. Just remember our deal.

06:29.639 --> 06:33.485
We finish this, you give us everything to start
new lives. Passport, cash, plane tickets.

06:33.643 --> 06:35.896
Believe me, if you succeed today...

06:36.104 --> 06:38.402
...you'll get everything you want and more.

06:39.232 --> 06:40.779
Good luck.

06:43.653 --> 06:45.405
[VAN DOORS CLOSE
THEN ENGINE STARTS]

07:01.421 --> 07:03.389
RYAN:
We need to be on high alert today.

07:03.590 --> 07:07.766
While we have disrupted Strauss' plan,
I'm afraid he might have a backup in place.

07:07.969 --> 07:13.146
Now, photos of Mark and Daisy and Kyle
have been circulated around the courthouse.

07:13.350 --> 07:14.647
Security has been increased.

07:14.851 --> 07:17.604
I've asked for HRT to be standing by
on the scene just in case.

07:17.812 --> 07:21.112
According to the prosecution,
Agent Hardy will testify first...

07:21.316 --> 07:23.660
...followed by the reporter, Carrie Cooke.

07:23.860 --> 07:25.783
RYAN:
I had a really nice time last night.

07:26.655 --> 07:27.781
Me too.

07:34.287 --> 07:36.836
I want the story, Ryan...

07:37.040 --> 07:38.542
...but I also wanna help you.

07:42.963 --> 07:46.217
She's staying at a hotel near the
courthouse with private security.

07:46.424 --> 07:49.223
When it's time for them to move,
U.S. Marshals Service...

07:49.427 --> 07:51.304
...will provide additional support.

07:51.513 --> 07:55.359
Mike, where are you with establishing a
link between Strauss and Daisy and Kyle?

07:55.558 --> 07:59.313
Agents in Ohio are looking for a
connection, but nothing so far.

07:59.521 --> 08:03.321
Key is gonna be figuring out how he was
able to communicate with them from prison.

08:03.525 --> 08:06.529
- Has to be a go-between.
- Agent Sloan, call Pine Mountain.

08:06.736 --> 08:10.411
Request visitor logs, run background checks
on everyone who's visited Strauss.

08:10.615 --> 08:12.037
Will do.

08:13.034 --> 08:15.253
I don't need to tell you
how important this is.

08:15.453 --> 08:19.708
Arthur Strauss,
he's the guy that taught Joe Carroll.

08:19.916 --> 08:22.795
He has mentored
an unknowable number of psychopaths.

08:24.254 --> 08:26.507
He is the father of serial killers...

08:26.715 --> 08:30.390
...and there'll be hell to pay
if he gets back in the world.

08:44.482 --> 08:46.484
[REPORTERS CHATTERING]

09:06.713 --> 09:09.057
MAN: Move it, move it. Let's go.
REPORTER 1: Agent Hardy.

09:09.215 --> 09:11.684
REPORTER 2: Excuse me, Agent Hardy...
REPORTER 3: Agent Hardy.

09:11.885 --> 09:13.853
REPORTER 4:
Just a question before you go...

09:14.054 --> 09:16.978
- Will you be testifying...?
REPORTER 5: Agent Hardy.

09:17.640 --> 09:19.483
REPORTER 6:
Agent Hardy...

09:21.603 --> 09:22.775
REPORTER 7:
Agent Hardy...

09:22.979 --> 09:26.734
We're at the federal courthouse in New
York City, where Dr. Arthur Strauss...

09:26.900 --> 09:29.528
...the man the FBI claims
is the mentor to Joe Carroll...

09:29.694 --> 09:33.870
...will face the jury on charges of kidnapping,
false imprisonment and attempted murder.

09:34.074 --> 09:36.577
Everyone who visited Strauss in jail
seems aboveboard.

09:36.785 --> 09:39.664
Other than coworkers,
they're all members of his legal team.

09:39.829 --> 09:43.834
Dig deeper, okay?
One of them has to be his go-between.

09:51.466 --> 09:54.094
- We need to talk about what happened.
- Not a good time.

09:54.302 --> 09:56.225
Max, I don't care.

09:56.429 --> 09:59.399
- It was real.
- Real or not, nothing has changed.

09:59.599 --> 10:03.274
You chose hunting Mark over me,
and you would do it again, wouldn't you?

10:07.649 --> 10:09.743
- Sheila.
- Agent Hardy.

10:09.943 --> 10:11.786
I hope you had a good breakfast.

10:11.986 --> 10:14.159
You're going to get a workout on the stand.

10:14.364 --> 10:16.958
- Second thoughts putting me up there?
- Hell, yes.

10:17.158 --> 10:19.786
Normally I avoid
relying on the testimony of a man...

10:19.994 --> 10:23.214
...whose name has been written in blood
calling him a liar.

10:23.414 --> 10:25.542
- Written by Strauss' followers.
- Got proof?

10:25.750 --> 10:28.378
Because without it,
I can't allege a criminal conspiracy.

10:28.586 --> 10:31.806
The defense is going to highlight
the black cloud over your head.

10:32.006 --> 10:34.100
Let them. I'm ready.

10:34.300 --> 10:35.893
You better be.

10:39.764 --> 10:40.856
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

10:42.350 --> 10:43.602
Morning. I'm Agent Johnson.

10:43.810 --> 10:45.778
- Good morning.
- Our asset is about to move.

10:45.979 --> 10:48.152
- I've been assigned as overwatch.
- Come on in.

10:48.356 --> 10:51.735
We've got Ms. Cooke isolated
on the 11th floor.

10:51.901 --> 10:53.653
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

11:01.995 --> 11:04.748
- Careful. Don't spill any blood.
- I got it.

11:07.250 --> 11:08.593
[KNIFE PIERCES FLESH]

11:09.794 --> 11:13.640
Okay, here we go. Carrie Cooke's room.

11:14.382 --> 11:16.555
Now for the hard part.

11:19.762 --> 11:23.187
I heard Carrie Cooke screaming.
I entered the defendant's home.

11:23.433 --> 11:25.811
Once inside, I was attacked, I was drugged.

11:26.019 --> 11:30.695
When I woke up, Ms. Cooke and I were
tied up and being held by Dr. Strauss.

11:30.899 --> 11:31.946
What happened then?

11:32.150 --> 11:34.403
After the defendant confessed
to harboring Joe...

11:34.611 --> 11:35.783
Objection.

11:35.945 --> 11:38.619
Stick to the facts before us, Agent Hardy.

11:40.200 --> 11:45.001
Dr. Strauss instructed his student
to break Carrie Cooke's feet...

11:45.163 --> 11:47.837
...with a Sledgehammer,
and then he threatened to kill us.

11:47.999 --> 11:49.967
- What stopped him?
- I was able to get free.

11:50.168 --> 11:53.638
With the help of Special Agent Mike Weston
and Max Hardy of the N.Y.P.D...

11:53.796 --> 11:56.845
...we took the defendant into custody.
- Thank you.

11:58.801 --> 12:01.975
Agent Hardy, where were you
when you heard Carrie Cooke screaming?

12:02.138 --> 12:03.811
Parked in my car outside the house.

12:03.973 --> 12:07.147
And yet none of Dr. Strauss' neighbors
heard those screams.

12:07.310 --> 12:10.530
- How do you explain that?
- I've been told I have very sensitive ears.

12:10.688 --> 12:14.158
It's a good thing. Because that screaming
is your only justification...

12:14.359 --> 12:17.488
...for entering the home of my client
without a warrant. Right?

12:17.946 --> 12:19.448
Yes.

12:21.658 --> 12:24.332
Five-minute warning,
then call the marshals and make our way in.

12:24.494 --> 12:26.542
- Copy that. How's Ms. Cooke?
- Nervous.

12:28.665 --> 12:30.258
Hey.

12:32.085 --> 12:35.180
- Look who I caught hiding in a stairwell.
- No.

12:35.338 --> 12:38.342
- Who is that?
- That girl feds are looking for. Give a hand.

12:41.261 --> 12:42.888
Nice shot.

12:45.223 --> 12:46.270
[GROANS]

12:46.432 --> 12:47.900
- You okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

12:50.853 --> 12:52.230
You ready?

13:01.072 --> 13:04.542
You, your FBI buddy and your niece
swooped down on Dr. Strauss' home...

13:04.701 --> 13:06.920
...without a warrant,
and then he disappeared...

13:07.120 --> 13:10.715
...rendition-style, for weeks, without
any opportunity to talk to a lawyer...

13:10.873 --> 13:13.547
...or to have the evidence
against him questioned. Right?

13:13.751 --> 13:16.504
His arrest was part of a larger
ongoing search for Joe Carroll.

13:16.713 --> 13:20.092
So the search for Joe Carroll
trumped my client's due-process rights?

13:20.258 --> 13:21.635
- I didn't say that.
- Didn't you?

13:21.801 --> 13:23.269
- Objection.
- Withdrawn.

13:23.511 --> 13:29.063
In order for the jury to convict my client,
they have to believe your account...

13:29.267 --> 13:30.314
And Carrie Cooke's.

13:30.560 --> 13:35.066
Yes, Carrie Cooke. Were you sleeping with
her at the time of Dr. Strauss' arrest?

13:35.273 --> 13:38.117
No, my relationship
with Ms. Cooke started...

13:38.318 --> 13:41.618
...after your client tried to murder us
in his basement.

13:41.821 --> 13:42.947
And it was public knowledge.

13:43.114 --> 13:45.833
NATHAN:
Your honesty has been called into question.

13:46.034 --> 13:49.914
At the fire-station massacre, you were
accused of lying. What was that about?

13:50.079 --> 13:53.424
You'd have to ask the psychopaths
that committed the murders.

13:53.583 --> 13:57.178
Well, your fellow FBI agent Jeffrey Clarke
stated in a video confession...

13:57.420 --> 14:01.050
Objection.
That confession was clearly coerced.

14:01.215 --> 14:02.762
That doesn't make it untrue.

14:04.969 --> 14:07.848
This is an e-mail exchange
between Agent Clarke...

14:08.097 --> 14:09.565
...and FBI Director Franklin...

14:09.724 --> 14:14.104
...dated just subsequent
to Dr. Strauss' arrest.

14:14.604 --> 14:17.699
- This wasn't entered into evidence.
- This just came into our possession.

14:17.940 --> 14:21.114
We contend that the state
withheld this document from discovery.

14:21.319 --> 14:23.947
What's the chain of custody?
What's the authentication?

14:24.113 --> 14:26.457
NATHAN:
This is an e-mail that originated...

14:26.616 --> 14:29.085
...from Agent Clarke's laptop,
which we have in evidence.

14:29.285 --> 14:33.836
I have a forensic expert ready to testify
to its authenticity.

14:34.082 --> 14:37.131
And Agent Clarke's wife, Anna...

14:38.503 --> 14:41.473
...is willing to testify
to the veracity of its contents.

14:41.672 --> 14:44.471
Agent Clarke shared his concerns with her.

14:44.634 --> 14:46.102
I'll allow it.

14:46.260 --> 14:49.013
Would you please read out loud
his e-mail for us?

14:52.225 --> 14:53.477
Having trouble?

14:53.643 --> 14:55.520
That's fine. I'll do it.

14:55.728 --> 15:00.825
Agent Clarke said he was worried that
Agent Hardy was, quote, "out of control."

15:01.025 --> 15:04.495
He said, "I believe Agent Hardy
has a personal vendetta against Strauss.

15:04.695 --> 15:06.823
He believes he is connected
to Joe Carroll."

15:06.989 --> 15:08.991
- This isn't Jeffrey.
NATHAN: The e-mail continues:

15:09.158 --> 15:11.160
"I think Hardy bugged Strauss' home."

15:11.327 --> 15:12.704
An illegal bug.

15:12.912 --> 15:16.212
That is how you really heard
what was happening in Dr. Strauss' home.

15:16.416 --> 15:18.009
Carrie was screaming...

15:18.167 --> 15:21.171
"Carrie Cooke backs up
Agent Hardy's account...

15:21.379 --> 15:25.009
...but they are close
and she will do anything for a big story."

15:25.174 --> 15:26.551
Clarke did not write this.

15:27.009 --> 15:31.264
Are we just supposed to accept
your good word on that, Agent Hardy?

15:32.598 --> 15:35.852
- I'm done with the witness.
- Your Honor, I need to get a short recess.

15:36.018 --> 15:38.146
WALLACE:
Five minutes.

15:39.397 --> 15:41.650
- Where'd that e-mail come from?
- It's a fake.

15:41.858 --> 15:44.031
They seem to be pretty confident
that it's not.

15:44.193 --> 15:47.447
And if you planted an illegal bug,
Strauss will walk.

15:47.655 --> 15:51.376
Our entire case against him will be
considered fruit of the poisonous tree.

15:51.534 --> 15:53.536
But if we prove that the
e-mail is not real...

15:53.744 --> 15:56.293
The jury's already heard it.
I can't unring that bell.

15:56.873 --> 15:59.547
All I can do is put
Carrie Cooke up there...

15:59.709 --> 16:04.806
...and hope the fact that you were sleeping
with her doesn't prejudice that jury.

16:07.967 --> 16:11.722
WALLACE:
AUSA, call your next witness, please.

16:14.056 --> 16:18.061
Your Honor, we're having trouble
locating my next witness, Carrie Cooke.

16:18.603 --> 16:21.903
NATHAN: Your Honor, it's mighty convenient
they can't locate her now...

16:22.064 --> 16:24.567
...that her entire testimony is in doubt.

16:24.775 --> 16:27.745
- This smells like a stall.
- Approach, please.

16:28.946 --> 16:30.789
[MOUTHS]
Find her.

16:36.245 --> 16:38.964
Your Honor, Carrie Cooke is the heart
of my entire case.

16:39.207 --> 16:41.255
Then I move for an immediate dismissal.

16:41.417 --> 16:45.763
My client has been held without bail for a
year. He has a right to a speedy trial.

16:45.963 --> 16:48.637
I give you one hour to find your witness.

17:04.773 --> 17:05.866
RYAN:
Carrie?

17:20.080 --> 17:22.630
Well, good night.

17:24.001 --> 17:25.252
Thank you, Ryan.

17:40.476 --> 17:41.523
WESTON:
Ryan.

17:41.769 --> 17:43.146
I'm in here.

17:44.522 --> 17:46.274
- Any sign of her?
- No.

17:46.440 --> 17:49.660
Place is clean. No sign of a struggle.
It's like they were never here.

17:49.819 --> 17:54.120
Security's last contact was 40 minutes ago
when the team was getting ready to move.

17:54.282 --> 17:55.499
[SNIFFS]

18:01.122 --> 18:02.715
- What is it?
- It's bleach.

18:04.000 --> 18:05.968
- You got a black light?
- Yeah.

18:22.727 --> 18:24.149
It's blood.

18:24.687 --> 18:26.360
They cleaned it up.

18:27.106 --> 18:29.985
WESTON: If Carrie or the team
were killed there, where are the bodies?

18:30.151 --> 18:31.869
And why bother cleaning it up after?

18:32.028 --> 18:36.955
Because Strauss knows that if there's a
body, Judge Wallace won't dismiss the case.

18:37.116 --> 18:40.245
- So Carrie could still be alive?
- If she is, she won't be for long.

18:40.453 --> 18:42.956
- Trial reconvenes in 20 minutes.
- Ryan.

18:43.748 --> 18:47.719
A security guard is also missing, and the
entire security system has been disabled.

18:47.877 --> 18:50.926
- Sounds like Daisy and Kyle's work.
- Kitchen worker saw a couple...

18:51.088 --> 18:53.056
...loading a cart into a laundry van.

18:53.215 --> 18:56.389
Got Sloan on the line, pulling CCTV
footage, see if we can track it.

18:56.552 --> 18:58.054
Give me the phone.

18:58.471 --> 19:00.690
Hey, what have you got?

19:01.724 --> 19:04.352
Van went north on Mercer
after it left the loading dock.

19:04.560 --> 19:07.188
- That was a few minutes ago.
- Let's go.

19:12.193 --> 19:13.240
[ENGINE STARTS]

19:14.904 --> 19:17.032
I picked it up again six minutes later.

19:17.239 --> 19:20.914
It's going eastbound in traffic
on the Williamsburg Bridge.

19:22.745 --> 19:26.045
Okay, it pulled into the old Navy Yard
five minutes ago.

19:34.048 --> 19:36.927
RYAN: Carrie!
MAX: Ryan, wait! Ryan.

19:37.134 --> 19:38.386
[GRUNTS]

19:38.928 --> 19:40.145
Ryan.

19:42.807 --> 19:44.434
RYAN:
Carrie.

19:45.434 --> 19:46.560
Ryan. Hey, Ryan.

19:46.936 --> 19:48.438
Ryan, I'm sorry.

19:58.322 --> 20:01.667
That fire hasn't been burning long.
Daisy and Kyle could still be close.

20:01.909 --> 20:03.161
Split up.

20:26.350 --> 20:29.354
Did you make sure everything's in the van?

20:29.812 --> 20:31.985
- Guns, IDs.
DAISY: Yeah, it's all there.

20:32.148 --> 20:34.651
Left to burn like Juliana said.

20:35.109 --> 20:37.532
I can't believe that we did it.

20:37.695 --> 20:39.663
We're free.

20:45.369 --> 20:46.837
[DAISY GASPS]

20:48.622 --> 20:49.669
Kyle, you're bleeding.

20:49.874 --> 20:52.002
I must have reopened the wounds.
No big deal.

21:00.384 --> 21:01.886
Kyle.

21:22.615 --> 21:24.242
KYLE:
I got it.

21:27.036 --> 21:29.004
- Come on, baby. You can do it.
- Aah.

21:31.248 --> 21:34.627
KYLE: Unh.
- Hurry. Come on, you can do it. Come on.

21:34.794 --> 21:38.890
- Go on, Daisy. You gotta go. Run.
- No. No. No, I'm not going without you.

21:39.131 --> 21:41.680
- I can't do this alone. No, come on.
- Yes, you can.

21:42.051 --> 21:44.850
Baby, you're the strongest woman
I've ever known.

21:45.679 --> 21:48.558
- I love you. I love you.
- I love you.

21:52.728 --> 21:54.355
- Okay.
- Go.

21:54.563 --> 21:56.406
Go. Come on.

22:06.742 --> 22:07.914
Drop the knife.

22:08.160 --> 22:09.252
Do it.

22:15.417 --> 22:17.090
Yeah, it's Carrie's.

22:17.586 --> 22:21.181
Innocent people's blood always seems
to come out a little bit darker.

22:21.382 --> 22:23.555
Did you ever notice that, Ryan?

22:24.093 --> 22:25.686
I bet you have.

22:25.886 --> 22:28.480
Drop the knife, get down on your knees.

22:29.390 --> 22:31.484
I'm not gonna ask you again.

22:32.726 --> 22:34.728
Sure thing, chief.

22:39.650 --> 22:40.947
[GUNSHOTS]

22:48.951 --> 22:50.498
Daisy.

23:04.967 --> 23:06.469
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

23:07.136 --> 23:09.230
- Ryan.
- Carrie Cooke was murdered...

23:09.430 --> 23:13.651
...along with her security team. It was
Daisy and Kyle, which means it was Strauss.

23:13.809 --> 23:15.937
- Ryan.
- Tell Judge Wallace. She's gotta know.

23:16.103 --> 23:17.650
Ryan, it's too late.

23:18.147 --> 23:20.821
Wallace dismissed the case
when we missed the deadline.

23:20.983 --> 23:22.656
What? Where's Strauss?

23:22.818 --> 23:24.161
He walked 20 minutes ago.

23:32.036 --> 23:34.255
And we've filed a restraining order
against Hardy.

23:34.413 --> 23:37.917
REPORTER [ON TV]: Dr. Strauss, how does it
feel to be walking out of court a free man?

23:38.125 --> 23:42.175
Honestly? It feels like justice.

23:42.338 --> 23:43.840
[REPORTERS CHATTERING ON TV]

23:44.006 --> 23:45.599
[RYAN GRUNTS]

23:50.012 --> 23:51.605
My office. Now.

23:52.222 --> 23:53.724
The three of you.

23:57.061 --> 23:58.187
Shut the door.

24:04.151 --> 24:07.030
Look familiar? It's Clarke's e-mail.
The one from court today.

24:07.196 --> 24:10.917
On our secure server, time-stamped
and logged like it's been here all along.

24:11.116 --> 24:12.618
Someone hacked in, put it there.

24:12.826 --> 24:15.079
Our cyber guys said
that's virtually impossible.

24:15.245 --> 24:19.125
But it gets worse. The DOJ is opening up
an official investigation into you three...

24:19.291 --> 24:21.259
...based on what happened in court today.

24:21.418 --> 24:23.386
- Call them. Tell them it was just me.
- No.

24:23.545 --> 24:26.924
It won't make a difference. Franklin
told me to suspend the three of you...

24:27.132 --> 24:28.975
...the minute I see you.

24:29.510 --> 24:32.434
Which I will do when I see you.

24:34.223 --> 24:35.725
Tomorrow morning.

24:36.350 --> 24:39.069
Connect Strauss to Daisy
and prove criminal conspiracy.

24:39.269 --> 24:41.021
You won't have tac or intel support.

24:41.230 --> 24:44.200
So if this thing goes sideways,
you're on your own.

24:44.400 --> 24:46.653
- Thank you, Gina.
- Don't thank me.

24:46.860 --> 24:49.704
I'm doing it to protect
this office, not you.

25:21.478 --> 25:22.695
[KEYPAD BEEPS]

25:22.855 --> 25:24.357
[LOCK BUZZES]

25:40.664 --> 25:42.166
[BUTTON CLICKING]

26:06.899 --> 26:08.276
[BELL DINGS]

26:24.208 --> 26:25.425
[KEYS JINGLE]

26:28.962 --> 26:30.430
Strauss is nowhere to be found.

26:30.631 --> 26:33.885
He disappeared the minute he left court.
His lawyers aren't talking.

26:34.093 --> 26:36.061
Finding him by morning
isn't gonna be easy.

26:36.261 --> 26:40.016
I forgot to mention this place doubles
as our secret clubhouse.

26:47.689 --> 26:48.781
Hey.

26:49.191 --> 26:52.786
- You okay, doc?
- Yeah. Sitting in the court today...

26:53.987 --> 26:56.081
I feel like you're not
telling me everything.

26:56.281 --> 26:58.500
- Listen, Gwen, I am telling you...
- Forget it.

26:58.659 --> 27:01.003
It's not the right time.
I shouldn't have said anything.

27:01.161 --> 27:04.381
- But we are gonna need to talk about it.
RYAN: Of course.

27:04.581 --> 27:07.084
As soon as this is over,
you can ask me anything.

27:07.292 --> 27:08.544
I promise.

27:08.752 --> 27:12.882
Okay. I think I found Strauss' go-between.
She's a paralegal on his defense team.

27:13.048 --> 27:16.723
Juliana Barnes. She visited him in jail more
often than anybody else, frequently alone.

27:16.927 --> 27:19.771
- She recently paid off 100 grand in debt.
- We gotta talk to her.

27:29.606 --> 27:31.574
Do you like ironing?

27:32.442 --> 27:35.742
Yeah, most people don't.
They think it's boring. I find it relaxing.

27:37.364 --> 27:39.332
The routine of it.

27:39.491 --> 27:43.166
You can just turn your brain off
and disappear.

27:43.328 --> 27:46.081
Ah! You just gotta be careful
not to burn yourself.

27:46.248 --> 27:47.374
[CRYING]

27:50.252 --> 27:51.925
Tell me about Daisy and Kyle.

27:52.087 --> 27:54.135
What's their connection to Strauss?

27:54.339 --> 27:55.966
They were Strauss' students.

27:57.801 --> 27:59.178
He trained them.

27:59.386 --> 28:00.638
Andrew too?

28:01.513 --> 28:02.935
Yeah.

28:07.978 --> 28:11.858
If they only cared about getting Strauss off,
why pretend to help me avenge my family?

28:12.024 --> 28:16.871
Because Andrew said
that you were the perfect patsy.

28:20.991 --> 28:24.245
With you involved, Ryan Hardy
and the FBI would never really know...

28:24.453 --> 28:26.296
...what was going on. No!

28:27.372 --> 28:28.874
I'm just the messenger.

28:29.082 --> 28:30.880
I'm not like them.

28:31.293 --> 28:34.843
Strauss paid me to make contact.
I thought it was harmless.

28:35.047 --> 28:37.391
When I realized what I was into,
it was too late.

28:37.591 --> 28:42.097
Look, normally I'd feel bad for you,
but I'm trying to toughen up.

28:43.805 --> 28:45.728
So let's get back on topic.

28:45.891 --> 28:47.063
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

28:58.528 --> 29:00.075
It's Maggie. Who's that?

29:00.239 --> 29:04.289
- She's a secretary at my firm.
- According to her, the FBI is at your office.

29:04.493 --> 29:07.963
So I guess I'm not the only one
who knows about you and Strauss.

29:08.121 --> 29:10.874
Which means we better hurry this up.
Ryan Hardy will be here soon.

29:11.041 --> 29:12.793
No.

29:16.797 --> 29:17.844
Awesome.

29:18.966 --> 29:22.015
I just thought of a great way
to kill two birds with one stone.

29:22.219 --> 29:26.520
But I'm gonna need you
to tell me where Strauss is.

29:26.682 --> 29:28.605
I can't.

29:29.309 --> 29:31.186
He'll kill me.

29:31.853 --> 29:36.199
Oh, wow. Are you slow?
Lady, you're already dead.

29:37.276 --> 29:40.120
It's really just a matter
of how bad it's gonna hurt.

29:42.489 --> 29:44.491
[CRYING]

30:02.301 --> 30:05.054
Looks like Strauss is covering his tracks.

30:16.064 --> 30:17.316
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

30:25.240 --> 30:26.958
There you are.

30:27.200 --> 30:28.747
I was starting to worry.

30:29.244 --> 30:31.087
Kyle is dead.

30:33.248 --> 30:34.795
It's your fault.

30:34.958 --> 30:36.960
[BOTH GRUNTING]

30:40.255 --> 30:41.882
[DAISY CRYING]

30:47.220 --> 30:50.349
You're emotional. I understand that.

30:52.601 --> 30:54.569
Kyle was a good man.

30:56.646 --> 30:58.774
Maybe not my brightest student...

30:58.940 --> 31:01.113
...but a loyal one.

31:02.778 --> 31:04.780
I promised him...

31:07.449 --> 31:11.499
...I would help you both start new lives
if you helped me.

31:11.745 --> 31:16.467
And I consider myself a man of my word.

31:16.625 --> 31:18.502
Still...

31:20.629 --> 31:25.806
...I know the idea of going on without him
must be difficult to accept.

31:26.009 --> 31:30.310
So I'm going to offer you a choice.

31:30.806 --> 31:35.812
I can end your pain right here and now...

31:36.019 --> 31:39.990
...and hopefully, you and Kyle can
be reunited in the afterlife.

31:40.190 --> 31:43.034
That is, if you believe that sort of thing.

31:43.819 --> 31:49.826
Or you can leave the country with me
and start over.

31:50.033 --> 31:55.506
Grieving for your lost love
from some nonextradition country.

31:57.624 --> 31:58.841
So...

32:00.419 --> 32:03.218
...which will it be?
- I'll go with you.

32:05.924 --> 32:08.643
That's the spirit.

32:12.806 --> 32:14.399
[STRAUSS CHUCKLES]

32:18.812 --> 32:20.530
Hey, I'm in her search history.

32:20.689 --> 32:22.862
She looked up directions
to Pier 46 in Red Hook.

32:23.066 --> 32:25.194
- How long ago?
MAX: Twenty minutes.

32:25.735 --> 32:27.578
- Why?
- Just seems a little amateur hour.

32:27.737 --> 32:31.207
- She doesn't know we'd look here first.
- She didn't plan on getting killed.

32:31.366 --> 32:34.916
- She thought she'd take her computer.
- So why would Strauss leave it behind?

32:35.078 --> 32:37.206
You can ask him when we catch him.

32:41.543 --> 32:45.389
Tell me, have you ever traveled by ship?

32:45.547 --> 32:48.221
Never been outside of Ohio
up until three weeks ago.

32:49.217 --> 32:50.764
Well...

32:52.387 --> 32:55.391
...in the right vessel, it can be heavenly.

32:55.891 --> 32:59.737
Sadly, our Ukrainian cargo ship...

32:59.895 --> 33:02.990
...is a far cry from the Queen Mary.

33:33.386 --> 33:34.433
FBI!

33:34.888 --> 33:37.937
Show me your hands!
Don't move! Hands in the air! Hey!

33:38.141 --> 33:39.939
Stop! Stop!

33:40.894 --> 33:42.396
Do not move!

33:45.607 --> 33:47.530
The look on your face right now...

33:47.734 --> 33:50.533
...makes what happened to me in court today
almost worth it.

33:50.737 --> 33:52.455
You think you've won?

33:53.031 --> 33:54.499
You haven't won anything.

33:54.658 --> 33:58.288
Daisy, Kyle, Andrew,
they're just the tip of the iceberg.

33:58.537 --> 33:59.789
I have students everywhere.

33:59.955 --> 34:03.129
They make Joe Carroll's followers
look like nothing.

34:03.291 --> 34:06.420
You, your niece, your girlfriend...

34:06.628 --> 34:08.471
...all die if I go back to prison.

34:08.630 --> 34:09.755
Shut up!

34:12.467 --> 34:14.969
Drop the briefcase. Drop it.

34:15.637 --> 34:16.934
Show me your hands.

34:17.097 --> 34:19.646
Two birds, one stone.

34:19.849 --> 34:21.476
Just like you planned.

34:24.603 --> 34:25.650
Mike!

34:25.813 --> 34:27.190
[GUNSHOT]

34:27.940 --> 34:29.864
[GUNFIRE]

34:42.664 --> 34:44.337
It's Mark. He's on the move.

34:44.498 --> 34:46.092
- I'm going after him.
RYAN: No!

34:46.293 --> 34:47.510
You and Max get Strauss.

34:47.668 --> 34:48.966
- Ryan.
RYAN: Don't argue.

35:23.204 --> 35:25.627
Hey! Hey!

35:26.041 --> 35:28.385
Stop! Put your hands up! Put them up!

35:42.724 --> 35:46.354
- Max, take Strauss to the car.
MAX: No, Mike! Mike, no!

35:47.562 --> 35:50.281
All right, start walking. Go.

35:52.275 --> 35:53.401
[MAX GRUNTS]

35:55.278 --> 35:57.201
[DAISY GRUNTING]

35:58.740 --> 36:00.242
Enough.

36:01.076 --> 36:02.578
Hurry up, uncuff me.

36:26.476 --> 36:28.149
[GUNFIRE]

36:28.311 --> 36:29.733
[GROANING]

36:42.617 --> 36:44.415
[GUNSHOT]

36:45.829 --> 36:47.172
[GUNSHOT]

37:08.309 --> 37:09.481
WESTON:
Hey! Hey!

37:09.686 --> 37:11.279
Where do you think you're going?

37:11.479 --> 37:12.822
There's no place to run.

37:20.196 --> 37:22.039
Get on your knees.

37:30.790 --> 37:33.168
We both knew it would end like this
for one of us.

37:33.334 --> 37:35.962
You had your chance and blew it.
Now it's my turn.

37:36.671 --> 37:38.264
Mike, stop!

37:38.465 --> 37:41.594
- Don't do it.
- You can't talk me out of this, Ryan.

37:41.801 --> 37:43.599
So walk away if you got a problem.

37:44.429 --> 37:47.228
RYAN:
It won't bring your father back, man.

37:47.390 --> 37:49.017
It won't end your pain.

37:49.225 --> 37:50.477
I don't care.

37:50.685 --> 37:51.937
I do.

37:52.187 --> 37:53.814
And so does Max.

37:58.985 --> 38:00.703
Mike. Mike.

38:00.862 --> 38:02.489
You're a good man.

38:02.655 --> 38:04.248
Don't let him strip that from you.

38:04.866 --> 38:08.086
- I have to do this. RYAN: You don't.
Pulling that trigger is easy.

38:09.204 --> 38:13.835
What I'm asking you to do is hard. It's harder
than anything you've ever done in your life.

38:14.083 --> 38:16.632
He doesn't deserve to live.

38:16.836 --> 38:19.555
But he does deserve to suffer.

38:20.298 --> 38:21.800
In an 8-foot cell...

38:22.425 --> 38:24.052
...23 hours a day.

38:24.260 --> 38:26.058
All alone, no friends, no visitors...

38:26.221 --> 38:29.065
...no chance of ever setting foot
outside that prison.

38:31.059 --> 38:34.859
You shoot him and his pain stops.

38:36.272 --> 38:38.149
Let him live...

38:39.400 --> 38:41.573
...and it never ends.

39:12.183 --> 39:14.026
What did you do?

39:14.644 --> 39:16.646
What did you do?

39:19.023 --> 39:20.775
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

39:21.901 --> 39:23.198
Max?

39:24.529 --> 39:26.782
DOCTOR:
Set her over there. What do you have?

39:26.990 --> 39:29.118
Female, head contusion, multiple trauma.

39:29.325 --> 39:31.669
Her BP is 78 over 58...

39:32.078 --> 39:33.830
Watch your back, people.

39:34.038 --> 39:35.085
Okay. We got it.

39:35.290 --> 39:37.509
- Bring her in here.
- Containment. Sorry.

39:37.709 --> 39:38.961
DOCTOR:
Take another room.

39:40.295 --> 39:41.922
You left her? You just left her?

39:42.088 --> 39:44.307
- I saw Mark. I went after him.
- She needed you.

39:44.465 --> 39:46.593
- I didn't know...
- That you should have her back?

39:46.759 --> 39:47.806
What were you thinking?

39:47.969 --> 39:51.439
I was gonna kill the man that murdered
my father. Until you got into my head.

39:51.598 --> 39:54.647
- It was the right thing to do!
- What about this feels right, Ryan?

39:54.809 --> 39:57.983
Max in here? Mark and Strauss out there?
Feels right to you?

39:58.187 --> 40:00.189
We look out for our own.
First and foremost.

40:00.398 --> 40:03.823
Okay, okay. Go ahead, fine.
Blame me for Max. You know what?

40:03.985 --> 40:07.535
If it had been you and we were chasing Joe,
you'd have done the same thing.

40:19.751 --> 40:22.379
WOMAN [OVER PA]:
Dr. Perry, phone...

40:22.587 --> 40:24.635
Dr. Perry, phone...

40:28.217 --> 40:30.515
- How is she?
- She's with the doctors.

40:30.720 --> 40:32.347
I can't get a straight answer.

40:32.847 --> 40:34.349
How are you holding up?

40:36.851 --> 40:38.569
Ryan, what is it?

40:39.062 --> 40:41.190
Before you got here...

40:42.357 --> 40:46.453
...I was thinking how much I needed a
drink. - You don't want to do that.

40:46.653 --> 40:48.451
- I messed up.
- This isn't your fault.

40:48.655 --> 40:52.125
I'm responsible for everything
that happened today. Everything.

40:52.659 --> 40:54.411
So fix it. Find a way.

40:56.955 --> 40:59.378
I just don't know if I can.

41:01.918 --> 41:04.888
I had a patient in the ER yesterday.

41:05.421 --> 41:06.764
Heart attack.

41:06.965 --> 41:08.717
He coded three times.

41:08.925 --> 41:10.268
I brought him back each time.

41:10.802 --> 41:13.146
The fourth time, I couldn't.

41:15.431 --> 41:17.525
He died on my table.

41:18.643 --> 41:22.648
If a patient codes tomorrow,
I'll try just as hard to bring him back.

41:23.815 --> 41:25.283
I won't give up...

41:25.483 --> 41:27.986
...no matter how impossible it seems.

41:34.283 --> 41:36.160
- Agent Hardy?
- How is she?

41:36.411 --> 41:39.915
Your niece suffered a concussion
and some internal trauma, but she's tough.

41:40.081 --> 41:41.583
She should make a full recovery.

41:42.375 --> 41:43.422
Thank you.

41:45.294 --> 41:46.967
That's great.

41:53.678 --> 41:55.351
What is it?

41:56.764 --> 41:58.812
I know what I have to do.

42:57.909 --> 43:00.583
What took you so long?

43:49.877 --> 43:51.879
[English - US - SDH]
